						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 7) set up in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Mahishāsuramardini temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulaśēkhara, 1344 A.D.</p>						

						<p>The badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 12[6]7, Tāraṇa, Mārggaśira ba. 3, Vṛiśchika 27, Thursday.</hi> The given details, bearing the week-day which was Tuesday, correspond to <hi rend="bold">1344 A.D., November 23,</hi> the Śaka year being current.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift of land to the goddess Bhagavatī of Niruvāra by the king.</p>						

						</summary>
